				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/weedfire24" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(4588247); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=4588247&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610203364" alt="weedfire24" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=4588247)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/weedfire24" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(4588247); return false;" >weedfire24</a></span> <span class="odate time_1576374861 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">15 Dec 2019 01:54</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4446668">
									

<p>I'll be honest, the main character really doesn't interest me as a person, and I don't think any amount of characterization will change that for me personally.</p>
<p>That said, this doesn't change the fact that this is one of the best tales and stories I've seen in a while and possibly the best newbie entrance on this site. I said it before but I was absolutely glued to my seat reading the latest page and was surprised when I looked at my monitor and learned 45 entire minutes had passed.</p>
<p>Have you written before? I feel like most people who join this site, join as complete newbies who've never written a short story in their lives, and yet you're able to produce some high quality writing immediately.</p>
<p>Good luck! I'll be following this closely.</p>
<p>EDIT: I know this goes against the &quot;theme&quot; of the page, but as someone who actually read Smile! before SCP-4581, I remembered feeling like I missed something quite important and it kind of confused me enough I stopped midway and went to read 4581 before reading the rest. I wouldn't recommend reading it in any other order than the way it was chronologically written. Tiny nitpick.</p>

							</div>

								
